So now we have the engine bay open. You can see the Continental as it is installed inside the tank.

00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:19.520
It's mounted on the brackets. There are four large bolts that are holding it in place.

00:22:19.760 --> 00:22:26.340
So if you wanted to pull the engine out, you'd undo the deck, lift that out of the way, lift up the engine

00:22:27.080 --> 00:22:30.180
by of course, disconnecting the power shaft, the fuel lines and what have you.

00:22:31.060 --> 00:22:36.700
This particular engine will get the tank up to a burst speed of 24 miles an hour and a sustained speed

00:22:36.760 --> 00:22:39.820
of about 21. Of course this was the weakest of the engine options.

00:22:40.240 --> 00:22:43.960
Later versions of the tank would go a  bit faster: up to 30.

00:22:44.640 --> 00:22:51.360
